nifesto for developing the conceptual tools to seek solutions to higher education’s most pressing issues. Hope Circuits aims to rewire mindsets, perspectives, and behaviours to in turn rewire and renew the systems within which university stakeholders learn, live, and work. It tackles this challenging feat by suggesting ten tools to build hope circuits, a concept borrowed from neuroscience.Riddell acknowledges that changing systems and deep cultures is not for the faint of heart; indeed, the more than 250 interviews conducted with thought partners for Hope Circuits expose how individuals who navigate complex systems regularly experience discomfort and even despair. In response, she shows us how to anchor a practice of hope in higher education with focus and intention, inviting others to adopt and adapt her approach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEducation, HigherzCanada. 0aEducational changezCanada. 7aEDUCATION / Administration / Higher.2bisacsh  aHigher.  aShakespeare.  aarts.  aauthentic.  abicameral.  achange.  acitizenship.  acivic society.  adesign.  aeducation.  afunding models.  agenerativity.  agovernance.  agrowth.  ahigh impact.  ahumanities.  ainclusive.  aleadership.  alearning.  aluminaries.  amanagement.  amentorship.  ametaphor.  amindset.  aparadigm shifts.  apurpose.  arenewal.  aresearch.  aresilience.  astudent-centered.  asystems thinking.  ateaching.  athought leaders.  avalue.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228020684?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228020684423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228020684/original  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  a